heaviest_rainfall.status: Today's storm ranked 7th for total rainfall with 22.32mm having fallen, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  8.3mm per hour fell at points during the storm which lasted 27.6 hours.  The heaviest total rainfall occurred on 09 November 2025, dropping 47.89mm of rain over the 144.8 hour storm duration with a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 27.6 hours on 09 November 2025 (ranking 8th from our records for the longest storm) and it produced a total of 22.32mm of rain at a maximum intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  The lengthiest precipitation event recorded spanned 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025, it was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 24.6mm per hour and a total rainfall of 47.89mm.
